Introduction

WayV is a six-member boy group under SM Entertainment. They are the Chinese and fourth overall sub-unit of NCT. Originally seven, they debuted in China on January 17, 2019, with their first digital EP, The Vision.

The members of WayV are Kun, Ten, Winwin, Xiaojun, Hendery, and Yangyang.

The group is produced by SM Entertainment but managed by their China-exclusive, Label V.

On May 10, 2023, it was announced that Lucas would be leaving the group along with the rest of NCT to pursue his individual endeavors.
